<div class="comparison-wrapper page-width">
  <div class="comparison-table">
    <div class="comparison-header">
      <div class="col-left">The Challenge</div>
      <div class="col-right">Barrel Myst One Hockey Stick</div>
    </div>

    <div class="comparison-row">
      <div class="col-left">• Frequent breakage due to weak construction</div>
      <div class="col-right">
        • Reinforced shaft walls and premium Japanese carbon fiber dramatically increase durability
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="comparison-row">
      <div class="col-left">• Marketing gimmicks with little real performance impact</div>
      <div class="col-right">
        • Scientifically engineered features like carbon bridges and optimized fiber orientation improve responsiveness
        and shot release
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="comparison-row">
      <div class="col-left">• Overly lightweight sticks that feel hollow or unstable</div>
      <div class="col-right">
        • Slightly increased weight (by ~30g) paired with a higher balance point for a stable, yet feather-light in-hand
        feel
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="comparison-row">
      <div class="col-left">• Poor energy transfer in cheap or poorly balanced sticks</div>
      <div class="col-right">
        • One-piece construction and balanced weight distribution maximize energy transfer and control
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="comparison-row">
      <div class="col-left">• Surface chips and early cosmetic damage</div>
      <div class="col-right">
        • Durable thin foil wrap adds a protective outer layer, extending lifespan and resisting impact damage
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="comparison-row">
      <div class="col-left">• Low-quality materials in budget/no-name sticks</div>
      <div class="col-right">
        • Uses aerospace-grade Japanese carbon, avoiding inconsistencies common in lower-tier Chinese composites
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="comparison-row">
      <div class="col-left">• Unnatural feel and poor puck control</div>
      <div class="col-right">
        • Carefully tuned flex profile and improved shaft geometry give elite-level feel and accurate handling
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="comparison-row">
      <div class="col-left">• Lack of trust in brand promises</div>
      <div class="col-right">
        • Built from real testing and collaboration with European engineers — not marketing fluff
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="comparison-row">
      <div class="col-left">• No customer support or post-purchase warranties</div>
      <div class="col-right">
        • Barrel offers responsive customer support and a transparent warranty policy, standing behind every stick we
        build
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

